@startuml datamodel
!theme plain
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

title Herold -- Datenmodell (SQLite)

' Strict subset of the D1 Persistent region (see d1-information-model)
' mapped to concrete SQLite columns. Framework tables
' (sessions, password_reset_tokens, cache*, jobs*) and framework-only
' columns (remember_token, email_verified_at) are intentionally not
' shown — they are Laravel scaffolding, not part of the domain model.

enum NoteStatus {
  recorded
  processed
  sent
  error
}

class voice_notes <<table>> {
  **id** : ULID <<PK>>
  --
  type : string
  status : string <<NoteStatus>>
  audio_path : string [nullable]
  transcript : text [nullable]
  processed_title : string [nullable]
  processed_body : text (markdown) [nullable]
  metadata : json [nullable]
  github_issue_number : integer [nullable]
  github_issue_url : string [nullable]
  error_message : text [nullable]
  created_at : timestamp
  updated_at : timestamp
}

class users <<table>> {
  **id** : bigint <<PK>>
  --
  name : string
  email : string <<unique>>
  api_key_hash : string [nullable]
  totp_secret : text (encrypted) [nullable]
  totp_confirmed_at : timestamp [nullable]
  created_at : timestamp
  updated_at : timestamp
}

' -- Relationships --

voice_notes ..> NoteStatus : status

note right of voice_notes
  Maps D1 **VoiceNote**.
  **type**: general | youtube | diary | obsidian | todo
  (open set, configured in ""config/herold.php"").

  Column-to-D1 mapping:
  - ""metadata"" persists D1 **VoiceNote.extraFields**
  - ""audio_path"" persists D1 **VoiceNote.audioPath**
  - ""github_issue_number"" / ""github_issue_url""
    persist D1 **VoiceNote.githubIssueNumber/Url**

  **metadata** (JSON) shape per type:
  - youtube: { youtube_url }
  - diary: { entry_date }
  - obsidian: { vault }
  - todo: { deadline }
  - general: {}
end note

note bottom of users
  Maps D1 **Operator**.
  Single-user system — at most one row.
  Enforced by SQLite trigger ""enforce_users_singleton""
  (BEFORE INSERT, RAISE ABORT when count >= 1).

  Authentication is **API key + TOTP**:
  - ""api_key_hash"" persists D1 **Operator.apiKeyHash**
    (SHA-256, constant-time compare)
  - ""totp_secret"" persists D1 **Operator.totpSecret**
    (Laravel cast ""encrypted"")
  - ""totp_confirmed_at"" persists D1 **Operator.totpConfirmedAt**

  Framework columns ""password"", ""remember_token"" and
  ""email_verified_at"" exist in the migration but are
  not part of D1's auth model — Herold does not verify
  passwords and does not use Laravel's remember-me or
  email-verification flows. They are omitted here.
end note

@enduml
